                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00 Elections/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. My 57, April 9, noon. Sixteen members of the Council of State met in secret
                    session this morning. It is reported that Nemours requested the members to adopt
                    the plan of the President’s Commission and elect Mr. Roy on April 14th. Mr. Leon
                    protested vigorously against such action and was greeted with applause.
                    Arguments and discussions against Nemours’ proposal followed. The closed session
                    lasted for 55 minutes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
